<HEADLINE>
FT  16 OCT 93 / Speed cameras cut road deaths
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SPEED cameras introduced just a year ago have helped reduce deaths and
serious accidents by more than 40 per cent, it was announced yesterday.
A network of cameras was installed in west London last October. The
Department of Transport said that in the first nine months fatal and serious
casualties had fallen by 41 per cent, casualties by 22 per cent and the
number of accidents by 24 per cent.
