FT  15 OCT 93 / International Company News: Strong third quarter for
Lockheed
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AGENCIES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
LOCKHEED, the US aerospace contractor, lifted third-quarter net profit to
Dollars 117m, or Dollars 1.85 a share, from Dollars 86m, or Dollars 1.40, in
the corresponding period last year, agencies report.
This brings net profit for nine months to Dollars 287m, or Dollars 4.57 a
share, which compares with a loss of Dollars 402m, or Dollars 6.48, in the
same period of 1992.
Last year's figures, however, reflect a significant accounting charge: net
earnings before the charge equalled Dollars 3.69 a share.
Nine-month revenues increased to Dollars 9.33bn from Dollars 7.18bn, with
the third quarter generating Dollars 3.47bn against Dollars 2.47bn.
The latest quarter's figures include a gain of about Dollars 90m on
settlement of the P-7A navy aircraft dispute, partly offset by changes of
about Dollars 75m for the discontinuance of certain operations.
