<HEADLINE>
FT  15 OCT 93 / UK Company News: HTR Japanese offer oversubscribed
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PHILIP COGGAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE FIRST investment trust launch by Henderson Touche Remnant, the recently
merged fund management group, has proved a success with the Pounds 100m
offer for subscription of HTR Japanese Smaller Companies Trust being
oversubscribed.
The amount raised, viewed in the light of the recent Pounds 60m flotation of
Fleming's Chinese trust and the Pounds 67m raised by Schroder's emerging
markets unit trust, indicates the healthy state of the collective funds
sector.
Henderson raised Pounds 75m via a placing for its trust with the Pounds 25m
coming from an offer for subscription. Dealings in the shares will start on
October 22.
</TEXT>
