<HEADLINE>
FT  15 OCT 93 / UK Company News: Pounds 1m buy for Tunstall
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
TUNSTALL, the emergency communications and security systems group, is
acquiring its Dutch distributor in a Pounds 1m deal.
Rotterdam-based Nieuwburg Care and Communications has acted as distributor
and installer of Tunstall's UK manufactured products in the Netherlands
since 1985.
The consideration, payable in cash from existing resources, comprises some
Pounds 450,000 for inventory and equipment and Pounds 550,000 for
outstanding orders.
In the 1992 year, Nieuwburg achieved turnover of Fl 4.38m (Pounds 1.6m) and
reported profits at break-even. Turnover for the 12 months to end-October
1993 will not be less than Fl 5m.
