<HEADLINE>
FT  15 OCT 93 / UK Company News: Clydeport buys Hunterston terminal
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Clydeport has bought the former Hunterston terminal in Ayrshire from British
Steel.
The announcement of the Pounds 4.8m deal followed an eight-week detailed
engineering study of the deep water facility. No traffics have been handled
through the Hunterston jetty since June 1992, following the closure of the
Ravenscraig steelworks.
