FT  15 OCT 93 / OFT clears Times over price cut
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE OFFICE of Fair Trading yesterday cleared The Times of predatory pricing
over its controversial 15p price cut to 30p on weekdays.
A formal complaint was made against the newspaper by The Independent which
has apparently suffered little if any circulation loss because of The Times
price cut.
Sir Bryan Carsberg, director-general of fair trading, said: 'I am satisfied,
on the basis of the information available, that the reduction in the cover
price of The Times reflects a calculated commercial decision by News
International (publisher of The Times) which I would not be justified in
treating as predatory.'
