<TEXT>
A FORMER Tory minister called last night for a cut in the number of British
troops in Northern Ireland. His comments threatened to weaken the
Conservative party's recently cemented understanding with the Ulster
unionists, David Owen writes.
Mr Archie Hamilton, the former armed forces minister, said British forces in
the province could be cut by a battalion - equivalent to about 600 men -
every year.
