<HEADLINE>
FT  15 OCT 93 / Uruguay Round draws fire from Perot camp
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NANCY DUNNE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
MR ROSS PEROT, the Texas billionaire, is refusing comment on a report that
he will pitch his political organisation, United We Stand, and his extensive
resources behind opposition to a Uruguay Round agreement, Nancy Dunne writes
from Washington.
A spokesman for United We Stand said he has not yet taken a position on the
Round, in order to focus his energies on defeating the North American Free
Trade Agreement. Mr Perot co-wrote a book detailing criticism of Nafta after
claiming, during the presidential debates, that 'a giant sucking sound'
would draw American jobs over the US-Mexican border.
His co-author, Mr Pat Choate, yesterday said he opposed Uruguay Round
provisions weakening US dumping laws and establish-ing a multilateral
trading organisation to oversee the world trading system.
Ms Lori Wallach, a prominent anti-Nafta organiser with Public Citizen, which
works closely with the Perot forces, said many of the same groups which
oppose the Nafta will also fight a Uruguay Round pact.
'Ross Perot feels about Nafta the way a vampire feels about garlic,' she
said. 'Ross Perot feels about Gatt the way a vampire feels about daylight.
One he regards with revulsion; the other means death.'
</TEXT>
