<TEXT>
President Clinton yesterday told representatives of the US film industry
that open markets for audio-visual industries must be included in any final
Uruguay Round agreement.
Mr Jack Valenti, head of the US Motion Picture Association, said the White
House was preparing to issue a statement that any deal must be 'fair and
just to American audio-visual'.
Mr Valenti was upset about French taxes on films which are used to subsidise
the French film industry. 'About 60 per cent of the subsidy money is taken
from theatres showing American films. We deserve a share of that.'
