<HEADLINE>
FT  15 OCT 93 / Israelis urged to free Palestinians
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JULIAN OZANNE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TABA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
ISRAELI and Palestinian peacemakers hammered out a comprehensive agenda on
security and civilian issues to implement a framework peace agreement
yesterday and set up a sub-committee to decide the fate of up to 11,500
Israeli-held Palestinian prisoners, Julian Ozanne reports from Taba.
On the second day of talks at the Egyptian Red Sea resort of Taba, the
Palestinian delegation, led by Mr Nabil Shaath, pressed the Israelis for the
quick release of Palestinian prisoners. The Israelis agreed to establish a
sub-committee to deliberate on prisoners, deportees and fugitives.
Both sides agreed an agenda for the talks, which resume in Taba next
Wednesday, but refused to make it public. Among the items known to be on the
agenda are the smooth transfer of power from the Israeli military
administration in the occupied territories to a Palestinian authority; the
territorial delimiting of the Jericho area which Israeli troops will quit;
and the timetable for Israeli military withdrawal from Jericho and Gaza.
