<HEADLINE>
FT  14 OCT 93 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Strength in demand for wool and gradually rising prices in recent weeks are
leading to more confidence. Clearances in Australia were again very good at
this week's auctions, and price increases were particularly marked among
superfine merinos at Goulburn. This sector has been leading the market
upwards for some time and stockpile availability is limited. There is a
widening view that the lowest point might have been passed in wool's long
and painful recession, and that stockpile disposal fears may have been
overdone. The AWC market indicator was 455 cents a kg on October 13, from
442 cents a week before.
