<HEADLINE>
FT  14 OCT 93 / International Company News: Boral drops Sagasco bid
conditions
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BORAL, the Australian building products and energy group, yesterday waived
some the technical conditions attached to its ADollars 760m (USDollars 502m)
takeover bid for Sagasco Holdings, the Adelaide-based gas producer, but made
no change to the ADollars 3.50-a-share offer price, writes Nikki Tait.
The dropping of the conditions gives Boral additional flexibility in the
latter stages of the bid contest, although the predator has maintained the
key 50.1 per cent acceptance condition.
Sagasco has already rejected Boral's bid as inadequate. Much now depends on
what the South Australian government decides to do with its remaining 31.8
per cent interest in Sagasco. Boral already owns 19.9 per cent of Sagasco,
bought from the state government, and purchase of the remaining interest
would be sufficient to give Boral control of its target.
</TEXT>
