<HEADLINE>
FT  14 OCT 93 / International Company News: Bankers Trust sets up Dollars
12m Angola oil facility
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANTONIA SHARPE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BANKERS Trust has structured and arranged a Dollars 12m facility which
provides protection against fluctuations in the price of crude oil for
Sonangol UEE, Angola's national oil company.
Sonangol has already drawn about 10 per cent of the one-year facility, which
will finance the installation of a floating production, storage and
offloading vessel so that two previously-drilled oil wells can be brought on
stream.
Bankers Trust has provided a hedge for about 2m barrels of crude oil. Mr Ted
Giletti, managing director of Energy Merchant Bank, part of Bankers Trust,
said the hedging mechanism was necessary because of the size of the facility
relative to the projected oil flow rate. The two wells are situated in Block
4/26, an offshore oilfield off the coast of Angola.
Block 4/26 is expected to produce between 7,000 b/d and 9,000 b/d and
recoverable reserves are estimated at between 9m and 14m barrels.
Since the mid-1980s, Angola has become the second-largest oil producer in
sub-Sahara Africa, after Nigeria. Bankers Trust said that further
development programmes are expected to boost Angola's crude oil production
from current levels of 500,000 b/d to about 700,000 b/d by 1997.
</TEXT>
