<HEADLINE>
FT  14 OCT 93 / UK Company News: NatWest to set up new Lloyd's trust
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD LAPPER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
NATWEST Markets Corporate Finance yesterday announced the formation of a new
Lloyd's investment trust.
The trust will be designed to raise as much as Pounds 75m in equity capital
to support the Lloyd's of London insurance market.
The Angerstein Underwriting Trust will be listed on the stock exchange and
is expected to invest in a range of Lloyd's syndicates.
NatWest has been working closely with Coutts, the private bank, and aims to
market the new trust to institutional and private investors.
Stace Barr Underwriting Agencies, an independent members' agent, will advise
Angerstein.
NatWest Wood Mackenzie will be broker and NatWest Investment Management will
be investment manager.
Mr Andrew Smithers, chairman of Angerstein, said: 'The proposed introduction
of corporate capital not only provides an opening to invest in Lloyd's,
without the risks of unlimited liability, but it comes at a time that
appears favourable for investors.'
</TEXT>
